TagHelpers.Name: Microsoft.AspNetCore.Components.Authorization.AuthorizeRouteView
TagHelpers.Documentation:
<summary>
             Combines the behaviors of <see cref="T:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Components.Authorization.AuthorizeView" /> and <see cref="T:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Components.RouteView" />,
             so that it displays the page matching the specified route but only if the user
             is authorized to see it.
            
             Additionally, this component supplies a cascading parameter of type <see cref="T:System.Threading.Tasks.Task`1" />,
             which makes the user's current authentication state available to descendants.
             </summary>

TagHelpers.Documentation: Button is a graphical user interface that helps to triggers an event on its click action. It can contain a text, an icon, svg or both. Button content is either by specifying property or by specifying content within tag directive. In the below code example, a basic button is initialized with property. ]]>

BoundAttributes.Name: ChildContent
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary> 
            Gets or sets a value that indicates the child content for the Button including HTML element. If the child content is not specified, button is rendered using <see cref="P:Syncfusion.Blazor.Buttons.SfButton.Content" /> property. 
            </summary> 
            <value> 
            The template content. The default value is <c>null</c>. 
            </value> 
            <remarks> 
            The child content which is specified within <see cref="T:Syncfusion.Blazor.Buttons.SfButton" /> tag directive is either a string or HTML Element. The string content is also specified using <see cref="P:Syncfusion.Blazor.Buttons.SfButton.Content" /> property. 
            </remarks>

BoundAttributes.Name: Content
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary> 
            Gets or sets a value that indicates the content of Button component. 
            </summary> 
            <value> 
            Accepts a string value. The default value is <c>String.Empty</c>. 
            </value> 
            <remarks> 
            Set child content within <see cref="T:Syncfusion.Blazor.Buttons.SfButton" /> tag directive, to render as HTML content. 
            </remarks>

BoundAttributes.Name: CssClass
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary> 
            Gets or sets a value that indicates the CSS class string to customize the appearance of button. 
            </summary> 
            <value> 
            Accepts a CSS class string separated by space to customize the appearance of button. The default value is <c>String.Empty</c>. 
            </value>

BoundAttributes.Name: Disabled
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary> 
            Gets or sets a value that indicates whether to enable or disable the button. 
            </summary> 
            <value> 
            <c>true</c>, if the button component is disabled. The default value is <c>false</c>. 
            </value>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnableRtl
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary> 
            Gets or sets a value that indicates whether to enable or disable the right to left direction for button. 
            </summary> 
            <value> 
            <c>true</c>, if the right to left direction is enabled for button. The default value is <c>false</c>. 
            </value>

BoundAttributes.Name: IconCss
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary> 
            Gets or sets a value that indicates the CSS class string to include an icon or image for the button.  
            </summary> 
            <value> 
            Accepts a CSS class string separated by space to include an icon or image for the button. The default value is <c>String.Empty</c>. 
            </value>

BoundAttributes.Name: IconPosition
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary> 
            Gets or sets a value that indicates how to display icons in the button. 
            </summary> 
            <value> 
            One of the <see cref="P:Syncfusion.Blazor.Buttons.SfButton.IconPosition" /> enumeration. The default value is <see cref="F:Syncfusion.Blazor.Buttons.IconPosition.Left" /> 
            </value> 
            <remarks> 
            If the <c>IconPosition</c> is <c>Left</c>, the icon will be placed left to the content of the button. 
            If the <c>IconPosition</c> is <c>Right</c>, the icon will be placed right to the content of the button. 
            If the <c>IconPosition</c> is <c>Top</c>, the icon will be placed above the content of the button. 
            If the <c>IconPosition</c> is <c>Bottom</c>, the icon will be placed below the content of the button. 
            </remarks>

BoundAttributes.Name: IsPrimary
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary> 
            Gets or sets a value that indicates whether to enable or disable the primary style for button. 
            </summary> 
            <value> 
            <c>true</c>, if the primary style is enabled for button component. The default value is <c>false</c>. 
            </value>

BoundAttributes.Name: IsToggle
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary> 
            Gets or sets a value that indicates whether to enable or disable the toggle option for button component. 
            </summary> 
            <value> 
            <c>true</c>, if the toggle option is enabled for button component. The default value is <c>false</c>. 
            </value>

            </value>

BoundAttributes.Name: Target
BoundAttributes.Documentation: Gets or sets the selector that points to an element in which the FAB will be positioned. The default value is null where FAB is positioned based on viewport of browser. The target element must have relative position, else FAB will get positioned based on the closest element which has relative position. Simple FAB with target. ]]>

BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary> 
            Gets or sets a value that indicates whether the FAB is visible or hidden. 
            </summary> 
            <value> 
            <c>true</c>, if the FAB is visible. The default value is <c>true</c>. 
            </value>

BoundAttributes.Name: Position
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary> 
            Gets or sets the value that indicates the position of the FAB relative to <see cref="P:Syncfusion.Blazor.Buttons.SfFab.Target" />. 
            </summary> 
            <value> 
            One of the <see cref="T:Syncfusion.Blazor.Buttons.FabPosition" /> enumeration that specifies the position of FAB. The default value is <see cref="F:Syncfusion.Blazor.Buttons.FabPosition.BottomRight" />.
            </value> 
            <remarks>
            To refresh the position of FAB on <see cref="P:Syncfusion.Blazor.Buttons.SfFab.Target" /> resized, use <see cref="M:Syncfusion.Blazor.Buttons.SfFab.RefreshPositionAsync" /> method. 
            The position will be refreshed automatically when browser resized.
            </remarks>

            Gets or sets a value that indicates the CSS class string to include an icon or image for the button.

            Accepts a CSS class string separated by space to include an icon or image for the button. The default value is <c>String.Empty</c>. 
            </value>

BoundAttributes.Name: IconPosition
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary> 
            Gets or sets a value that indicates how to display icons in the button. 
            </summary> 
            <value> 
            One of the <see cref="P:Syncfusion.Blazor.Buttons.SfButton.IconPosition" /> enumeration. The default value is <see cref="F:Syncfusion.Blazor.Buttons.IconPosition.Left" /> 
            </value> 
            <remarks> 
            If the <c>IconPosition</c> is <c>Left</c>, the icon will be placed left to the content of the button. 
            If the <c>IconPosition</c> is <c>Right</c>, the icon will be placed right to the content of the button. 
            If the <c>IconPosition</c> is <c>Top</c>, the icon will be placed above the content of the button. 
            If the <c>IconPosition</c> is <c>Bottom</c>, the icon will be placed below the content of the button. 
            </remarks>

            </summary>

TagHelpers.Name: Syncfusion.Blazor.Buttons.SfSpeedDial
TagHelpers.Documentation:
The Blazor SpeedDial component that appears in front of all the contents of the page and displays list of action buttons on click which is an extended version of FAB. The button of speed dial is positioned in relative to a view port of browser or . It can display a menu of related actions or a custom content . A simple SpeedDial with action items. ]]> A SpeedDial with popup template.

Feedback Form

Name

Leave Your Comments
]]>

BoundAttributes.Name: CloseIconCss
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary> 
            Gets or sets one or more CSS classes to include an icon or image to denote the speed dial is opened and displaying menu items.
            </summary> 
            <value> 
            Accepts a CSS class string separated by space to include an icon or image for the button. The default value is String.Empty.
            </value> 
            <remarks> 
            If the `CloseIconCss` is <c>String.Empty</c>, then the <see cref="P:Syncfusion.Blazor.Buttons.SfSpeedDial.OpenIconCss" /> is used when SpeedDial is open as well.
            </remarks>

BoundAttributes.Name: Content
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary> 
            Gets or sets the content for the button of SpeedDial. 
            </summary> 
            <value> 
            Accepts a string value. The default value is <c>String.Empty</c>. 
            </value>

BoundAttributes.Name: CssClass
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary> 
            Gets or sets one or more CSS classes to customize the appearance of SpeedDial. 
            </summary> 
            <value> 
            Accepts a CSS class string separated by space to customize the appearance of button. The default value is <c>String.Empty</c>. 
            </value>

BoundAttributes.Name: Direction
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Gets or sets the value that indicates the speed dial action items (<see cref="T:Syncfusion.Blazor.Buttons.SpeedDialItems" />) display direction when <see cref="P:Syncfusion.Blazor.Buttons.SfSpeedDial.Mode" /> is <see cref="F:Syncfusion.Blazor.Buttons.SpeedDialMode.Linear" />. 
            </summary> 
            <value> 
            One of the <see cref="T:Syncfusion.Blazor.Buttons.LinearDirection" /> enumeration that specifies the direction of speed dial items in linear mode. The default value is <see cref="F:Syncfusion.Blazor.Buttons.LinearDirection.Auto" />
            </value>

BoundAttributes.Name: Disabled
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary> 
            Gets or sets a value that indicates whether to enable or disable the SpeedDial. 
            </summary> 
            <value> 
            <c>true</c>, if the button component is disabled. The default value is <c>false</c>. 
            </value>

BoundAttributes.Name: Mode
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Gets or sets the value that indicates the display mode (linear and radial mode) of speed dial action items. 
            </summary> 
            <value> 
            One of the <see cref="T:Syncfusion.Blazor.Buttons.SpeedDialMode" /> enumeration that specifies how the speed dial items are displayed. The default value is <see cref="F:Syncfusion.Blazor.Buttons.SpeedDialMode.Linear" />
            </value>

BoundAttributes.Name: IsModal
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Gets or sets the value that indicates whether the speeddial popup can be displayed as modal or modal less.
            </summary>
            <value> 
            <c>true</c>, if the Speed dial creates an overlay that disables interaction with other elements other than speed dial items. 
            If user clicks anywhere other than speed dial items then popup will get closed.
            The default value is <c>false</c>. 
            </value>

BoundAttributes.Name: ItemTemplate

BoundAttributes.Name: OverscanCount
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Gets or sets a value that determines how many additional items will be rendered
            before and after the visible region. This help to reduce the frequency of rendering
            during scrolling. However, higher values mean that more elements will be present
            in the page.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: SpacerElement
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
             Gets or sets the tag name of the HTML element that will be used as the virtualization spacer.
             One such element will be rendered before the visible items, and one more after them, using
             an explicit "height" style to control the scroll range.
            
             The default value is "div". If you are placing the <see cref="T:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Components.Web.Virtualization.Virtualize`1" /> instance inside
             an element that requires a specific child tag name, consider setting that here. For example when
             rendering inside a "tbody", consider setting <see cref="P:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Components.Web.Virtualization.Virtualize`1.SpacerElement" /> to the value "tr".
             </summary>

TagHelpers.Name: Syncfusion.Blazor.Popups.DialogAnimationSettings
TagHelpers.Documentation:
<summary>
            The class provides data for the animation to Dialog.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Delay
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the delay in milliseconds to start the animation.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Duration
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the duration in milliseconds that the animation takes to open or close the dialog.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Effect
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the animation name that should be applied on while opening and closing the dialog.
            If the user sets Fade animation, the dialog will open with the `FadeIn` effect and close with the `FadeOut` effect.
            The following are the list of animation effects available to configure to the dialog:
            1. Fade
            2. FadeZoom
            3. FlipLeftDown
            4. FlipLeftUp
            5. FlipRightDown
            6. FlipRightUp
            7. FlipXDown
            8. FlipXUp
            9. FlipYLeft
            10. FlipYRight
            11. SlideBottom
            12. SlideLeft
            13. SlideRight
            14. SlideTop
            15. Zoom
            16. None.
            </summary>

<summary>
            Provides data to configure the Dialog button properties.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ChildContent
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Gets or sets the content of the Spinner element.
            </summary>
            <exclude />

BoundAttributes.Name: Content
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Defines the text `content` of the Button element.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: CssClass
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Defines the class/multiple classes separated by a space in the Button element.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Disabled
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies a value that indicates whether the Button is `disabled`.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnableRtl
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Enable or disable rendering component in the right to left (RTL) direction.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: IconCss
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Defines the class/multiple classes separated by a space for the Button that is used to include an icon.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: IconPosition
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Positions the icon before or after the text content in the Button.
            The possible values are: Left: The icon will be positioned to the left of the text content.
            Right: The icon will be positioned to the right of the text content.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: IsPrimary
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Allows the appearance of the Button to be enhanced and visually appealing when set to `true`.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: IsToggle
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Makes the Button toggle, when set to `true`.
            When you click it, the state changes from normal to active.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: OnClick
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Event triggers when `click` the dialog button.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Type
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the type of the button.
            Possible values are Button, Submit, and Reset.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: IsFlat
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the Flat appearance of the dialog buttons.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: HtmlAttributes
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<exclude />
            <summary>
            You can add the additional html attributes such as id, title etc., to the button element.
            </summary>

TagHelpers.Name: Syncfusion.Blazor.Popups.SfDialog
TagHelpers.Documentation:
<summary>
            Represents the dialog component that displays the information and gets input from the user.
            Two types of dialog components are `Modal and Modeless(non-modal)` depending on their interaction with the parent application.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ID
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the unique identifier.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ChildContent
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Sets content for the Dialog element including HTML support and its customizations.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: AllowDragging
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the value whether the dialog component can be dragged by the end-user.
            The dialog allows a user to drag by selecting the header and dragging it for re-positioning the dialog.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: CloseOnEscape
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the Boolean value whether the dialog can be closed on pressing the escape (ESC) key.
            that is used to control the dialog's closing behavior.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Content
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the value that can be displayed in the dialog's content section.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: CssClass
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the CSS class name that can be appended with the root element of the dialog.
            One or more custom CSS classes can be added to a dialog.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnableResize
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the value whether the dialog component can be resized by the end-user.
            If the enableResize is true, the dialog component creates a grip to resize it in a diagonal direction.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ResizeHandles
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the resize handles direction in the dialog component that can be resized by the end-user.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnableRtl
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Enable or disable rendering component in the right to left (RTL) direction.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: FooterTemplate
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the template value that can be displayed with the dialog's footer area.
            This is an optional property and can be used only when the footer is occupied with information or custom components.
            By default, the footer is configured with the action buttons.
            If the footer template is configured to the dialog, the buttons property will be disabled.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Header
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the value that can be displayed in the dialog's title area that can be configured with a plain text.
            The dialog will be displayed without the header if the header property is null.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Height
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the height of the dialog component.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: HtmlAttributes
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            You can add the additional Html attributes such as id, title, etc., to the dialog element.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: IsModal
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the Boolean value whether the dialog can be displayed as modal or non-modal.
            `Modal`: It creates an overlay that disables interaction with the parent application and
             the user who should respond with modal before continuing with other applications.
            `Modeless`: It does not prevent user interaction with the parent application.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: MinHeight
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the min-height of the dialog component.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ShowCloseIcon
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the value that represents whether the close icon can be shown in the dialog’s title section.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Target
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the target element in which the dialog should be displayed.
            The default value is null, which refers to the `Document.body` element.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Visible
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the value that represents whether the dialog component is visible.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: VisibleChanged
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Gets or sets a callback of the bound value.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Width
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the width of the dialog.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ZIndex
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the z-order for rendering that determines whether the dialog is displayed
            in front or behind of another component.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: AllowPrerender
BoundAttributes.Documentation: Gets or sets whether the Dialog element re-render or not when the Dialog gets open. true, if dialog component elements are maintained on the DOM when closing and opening it; otherwise, false.The default value is false. Disabling this property, the Dialog component DOM element will be destroyed when closing and re-rendered the dialog DOM element while opening it. Otherwise, the dialog will be shown when opening it and remain hidden while closing it when enabled.

            Specifies the value that can be displayed in the dialog's title area that can be configured with a plain text.
            The dialog will be displayed without the header if the header property is null.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Height
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the height of the dialog component.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: HtmlAttributes
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            You can add the additional Html attributes such as id, title, etc., to the dialog element.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: IsModal
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the Boolean value whether the dialog can be displayed as modal or non-modal.
            `Modal`: It creates an overlay that disables interaction with the parent application and
             the user who should respond with modal before continuing with other applications.
            `Modeless`: It does not prevent user interaction with the parent application.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: MinHeight
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the min-height of the dialog component.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ShowCloseIcon
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the value that represents whether the close icon can be shown in the dialog’s title section.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Target
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the target element in which the dialog should be displayed.
            The default value is null, which refers to the `Document.body` element.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Visible
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the value that represents whether the dialog component is visible.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: VisibleChanged
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Gets or sets a callback of the bound value.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Width
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the width of the dialog.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ZIndex
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the z-order for rendering that determines whether the dialog is displayed
            in front or behind of another component.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: AllowPrerender
BoundAttributes.Documentation: Gets or sets whether the Dialog element re-render or not when the Dialog gets open. true, if dialog component elements are maintained on the DOM when closing and opening it; otherwise, false.The default value is false. Disabling this property, the Dialog component DOM element will be destroyed when closing and re-rendered the dialog DOM element while opening it. Otherwise, the dialog will be shown when opening it and remain hidden while closing it when enabled.

TagHelpers.Name: Syncfusion.Blazor.Popups.SfDialogProvider
TagHelpers.Documentation:
<summary>
            DialogProvider is a target element where the built-in dialogs are shown using <see cref="M:Syncfusion.Blazor.Popups.SfDialogService.ConfirmAsync(System.String,System.String,Syncfusion.Blazor.Popups.DialogOptions)" />,
            <see cref="M:Syncfusion.Blazor.Popups.SfDialogService.AlertAsync(System.String,System.String,Syncfusion.Blazor.Popups.DialogOptions)" /> and <see cref="M:Syncfusion.Blazor.Popups.SfDialogService.PromptAsync(System.String,System.String,Syncfusion.Blazor.Popups.DialogOptions)" /> 
            methods that are appended to this element. 
            </summary>
            <remarks>
            It is recommended to add this component in `MainLayout.razor` to show utility dialogs from anywhere in the application.
            If you add this to any particular page, the utility dialogs can then be displayed only for that page.
            </remarks>

TagHelpers.Name: Syncfusion.Blazor.Popups.SfTooltip
TagHelpers.Documentation:
<summary>
            The SfTooltip component displays a pop-up containing information or a message when you hover, click, focus, or touch an element.
            </summary>
            <summary>
            The SfTooltip component displays a pop-up containing information or a message when you hover, click, focus, or touch an element.
            </summary>
            <summary>
            The SfTooltip component displays a pop-up containing information or a message when you hover, click, focus, or touch an element.
            </summary>
            <summary>
            The SfTooltip component displays a pop-up containing information or a message when you hover, click, focus, or touch an element.
            </summary>
            <summary>
            The SfTooltip component displays a pop-up containing information or a message when you hover, click, focus, or touch an element.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Closed
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The event `Closed` will be fired when the Tooltip component gets closed.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Opened
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The event `Opened` will be fired after the Tooltip component gets opened.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: OnClose
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The event `OnClose` will be fired before the Tooltip hides from the screen.
            The Tooltip close can be prevented by setting the cancel argument value to true.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: OnCollision
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The event `OnCollision` will be fired for every collision fit calculation.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: OnOpen
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The event `OnOpen` will be fired before the Tooltip is displayed over the target element.
            When one of its arguments `cancel` is set to true, the Tooltip display can be prevented.
            This event is mainly used to refresh the Tooltip positions dynamically or to set customized styles in it and so on.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: OnRender
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The event `OnRender` will be fired before the Tooltip and its contents will be added to the DOM.
            When one of its arguments `cancel` is set to true, the Tooltip can be prevented from rendering on the page.
            This event is mainly used to customize the Tooltip before it shows up on the screen.
            For example, to load the AJAX content or to set new animation effects on the Tooltip, this event can be opted.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Created
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The event `Created` will be fired after the Tooltip component is created.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Destroyed
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The event `Destroyed` will be fired when the Tooltip component is destroyed.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ChildContent
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<exclude />
            <summary>
            Defines the content which has to be passed.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ID
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<exclude />
            <summary>
            Defines the Id of the Tooltip component.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Animation
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            It is used to customize the animation of the Tooltip while opening and closing.
            The animation property also allows you to set delay, duration, and various other effects of your choice.
            You can set the same or different animation options to the Tooltip when it is in the open or close state.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: CloseDelay
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            To close the Tooltip after a specified delay in millisecond.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Content
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            To display the content of the Tooltip which can be a string element.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: CssClass
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            To customize the Tooltip which accepts the custom CSS class names that define specific
            user-defined styles and themes to be applied to the Tooltip element.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnableHtmlSanitizer
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            This property has been deprecated as we achieve this behavior by using ChildContent of render fragment type and and Content as a string value.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnablePersistence
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            As there are no properties required to persist in tooltip component, this property is deprecated.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnableRtl
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            To enable or disable the rendering component in the right to left direction.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: WindowCollision
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            It is used to set the collision target element as page viewport (window) or Tooltip element, when using the target.
            If this property is enabled, tooltip will perform the collision calculation between the target elements.
            and viewport(window) instead of Tooltip element.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Height
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            To set the height of the Tooltip component which accepts the string values.
            When the Tooltip content gets overflowed due to the height value, then the scroll mode will be enabled.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: IsSticky
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            To display the Tooltip in an open state until it is closed manually.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: MouseTrail
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            It allows the Tooltip to follow the mouse pointer moves over the specified target element.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: OffsetX
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            It sets the space between the target and Tooltip element in X-axis.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: OffsetY
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            It sets the space between the target and Tooltip element in Y-axis.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: OpenDelay
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            To open the Tooltip after a specified delay in millisecond.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: OpensOn
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            To determine the type of open mode to display the Tooltip content.
            The available open modes are Auto, Hover, Click, Focus, and Custom.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Position
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            To set the position of the Tooltip element with respect to the Target element.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ShowTipPointer
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            To show or hide the tip pointer of the Tooltip.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Target
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            To denote the target selector where the Tooltip needs to be displayed.
            The target element is considered as the parent container.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Container
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            It is used to set the container element in which the Tooltip’s pop-up will be appended.
            It's default value is `body`, in which the Tooltip’s pop-up will be appended.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: TipPointerPosition
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            It is used to customize the position of the tip pointer on the tooltip. The available options are Auto, Start, Middle, and End.
            When set to auto, the tip pointer gets auto adjusted within the space of the target's length and does not point outside.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Width
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            To set the width of the Tooltip component which accepts a string value.
            When set to auto, the Tooltip width gets auto adjusted to display its content within the viewable screen.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: HtmlAttributes
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Adds the additional html attributes to the Tooltip element.
            </summary>

TagHelpers.Name: Syncfusion.Blazor.DataManager
TagHelpers.Documentation:
<summary>
            The DataManager is a data management component used for performing data operations in applications.
            It acts as an abstraction for using local data source - IEnumerable and remote data source - web services returning JSON or oData.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: HttpClientInstance
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the HttpClient instance to be used  by DataManager.
            </summary>
            <remarks>Use HttpClientInstance property to inject named HttpClient into DataManager.</remarks>

BoundAttributes.Name: Url
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the endpoint URL. DataManager requests this URL when data is needed.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: AdaptorInstance
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the custom adaptor class type. DataManager uses this type value to instantiate custom adaptor class.
            </summary>
            <remarks>DataManager uses Activator.CreateInstance method to create custom adaptor instance.
            Injecting services into custom adaptor class, is not supported while using this approach.
            To inject and use services, provide custom adaptor as a Blazor component by extending DataAdaptor class.</remarks>

BoundAttributes.Name: Adaptor
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Gets or sets the data adaptor to be used by DataManager.
            <list type="bullet">
            <item>
            <term>BlazorAdaptor</term>
            <description>Default. BlazorAdaptor is used to process Enumerable data. It contains methods to process the given collection based on the queries.</description>
            </item>
            <item>
            <term>ODataAdaptor</term>
            <description>
            OData Adaptor provies ability to consume and manipulate data from OData services.
            </description>
            </item>
            <item>
            <term>ODataV4Adaptor</term>
            <description>
            ODatav4 Adaptor provies ability to consume and manipulate data from OData v4 services
            </description>
            </item>
            <item>
            <term>WebApiAdaptor</term>
            <description>
            WebApi Adaptor provies ability to consume and manipulate data from WebApi services.
            This adaptor is targeted to interact with Web API created using OData endpoint, it is extended from ODataAdaptor
            </description>
            </item>
            <item>
            <term>UrlAdaptor</term>
            <description>
            URL Adaptor is used when you are required to interact with all kind of remote services to retrieve data.
            </description>
            </item>
            <item>
            <term>RemoteSaveAdaptor</term>
            <description>
            Remote Save Adaptor is used for binding JSON data.
            It interacts with remote services only for CRUD operations.
            </description>
            </item>
            <item>
            <term>CustomAdaptor</term>
            <description>
            CustomAdaptor specifies that own data query and manipulation logic has been provided using custom adaptor component
            extended from DataAdaptor class.
            </description>
            </item>
            <item>
            <term>JsonAdaptor</term>
            <description>
            JsonAdaptor is used to process JSON data at the client side. It contains methods to process the given JSON data based on the queries.
            </description>
            </item>
            </list>
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: DataAdaptor
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Holds adaptor instance.
            </summary>
            <exclude />

BoundAttributes.Name: InsertUrl
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the insert URL.
            </summary>
            <remarks>Applicable for remote adaptors.
            When Insert method is called, request will be made to InsertUrl.
            If InsertUrl is not provided, Url is used as fallback.</remarks>

BoundAttributes.Name: RemoveUrl
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the remove URL.
            </summary>
            <remarks>Applicable for remote adaptors.
            When Remove method is called, request will be made to RemoveUrl.
            If RemoveUrl is not provided, Url is used as fallback.</remarks>

BoundAttributes.Name: UpdateUrl
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the update URL.
            </summary>
            <remarks>Applicable for remote adaptors.
            When Update method is called, request will be made to UpdateUrl.
            If UpdateUrl is not provided, Url is used as fallback.</remarks>

BoundAttributes.Name: CrudUrl
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the CRUD URL.
            </summary>
            <remarks>Applicable for remote adaptors.
            When Insert, Remove or Update method is called, request will be made to CrudUrl.
            If CrudUrl is not provided, Url is used as fallback.</remarks>

BoundAttributes.Name: BatchUrl
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the batch url.
            </summary>
            <remarks>Applicable for remote adaptors.
            When SaveChanges method is called, request will be made to BatchUrl.
            If BatchUrl is not provided, Url is used as fallback.</remarks>

BoundAttributes.Name: Json
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the IEnumerable collection. This data could be queried and manipulated.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Headers
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the key/value pair of headers.
            </summary>
            <remarks>
            Use Headers to add any custom headers to the request made by DataManager.
            Users can also send authentication bearer token using Headers property.
            </remarks>

BoundAttributes.Name: Accept
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the accept type.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Data
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the IEnumerale data.
            </summary>
            <exclude />

BoundAttributes.Name: TimeTillExpiration
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the time limit to clear the cached data.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: CachingPageSize
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>

TagHelpers.Name: Syncfusion.Blazor.DataManager
TagHelpers.Documentation:
<summary>
            The DataManager is a data management component used for performing data operations in applications.
            It acts as an abstraction for using local data source - IEnumerable and remote data source - web services returning JSON or oData.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: HttpClientInstance
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the HttpClient instance to be used  by DataManager.
            </summary>
            <remarks>Use HttpClientInstance property to inject named HttpClient into DataManager.</remarks>

BoundAttributes.Name: Url
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the endpoint URL. DataManager requests this URL when data is needed.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: AdaptorInstance
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the custom adaptor class type. DataManager uses this type value to instantiate custom adaptor class.
            </summary>
            <remarks>DataManager uses Activator.CreateInstance method to create custom adaptor instance.
            Injecting services into custom adaptor class, is not supported while using this approach.
            To inject and use services, provide custom adaptor as a Blazor component by extending DataAdaptor class.</remarks>

BoundAttributes.Name: Adaptor
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Gets or sets the data adaptor to be used by DataManager.
            <list type="bullet">
            <item>
            <term>BlazorAdaptor</term>
            <description>Default. BlazorAdaptor is used to process Enumerable data. It contains methods to process the given collection based on the queries.</description>
            </item>
            <item>
            <term>ODataAdaptor</term>
            <description>
            OData Adaptor provies ability to consume and manipulate data from OData services.
            </description>
            </item>
            <item>
            <term>ODataV4Adaptor</term>
            <description>
            ODatav4 Adaptor provies ability to consume and manipulate data from OData v4 services
            </description>
            </item>
            <item>
            <term>WebApiAdaptor</term>
            <description>
            WebApi Adaptor provies ability to consume and manipulate data from WebApi services.
            This adaptor is targeted to interact with Web API created using OData endpoint, it is extended from ODataAdaptor
            </description>
            </item>
            <item>
            <term>UrlAdaptor</term>
            <description>
            URL Adaptor is used when you are required to interact with all kind of remote services to retrieve data.
            </description>
            </item>
            <item>
            <term>RemoteSaveAdaptor</term>
            <description>
            Remote Save Adaptor is used for binding JSON data.
            It interacts with remote services only for CRUD operations.
            </description>
            </item>
            <item>
            <term>CustomAdaptor</term>
            <description>
            CustomAdaptor specifies that own data query and manipulation logic has been provided using custom adaptor component
            extended from DataAdaptor class.
            </description>
            </item>
            <item>
            <term>JsonAdaptor</term>
            <description>
            JsonAdaptor is used to process JSON data at the client side. It contains methods to process the given JSON data based on the queries.
            </description>
            </item>
            </list>
            </summary>

TagHelpers.Name: Syncfusion.Blazor.SplitButtons.ButtonGroupButton
TagHelpers.Documentation:
<summary> 
            Button Group Button component is creates a button component which is a graphical user interface that helps to triggers an event on its click action. 
            It can contain a text, an icon, svg or both. 
            </summary> 
            <remarks> 
            The button content is either by specifying <see cref="P:Syncfusion.Blazor.SplitButtons.ButtonGroupButton.Content" /> property or by specifying content within <see cref="T:Syncfusion.Blazor.SplitButtons.ButtonGroupButton" /> tag directive. 
            </remarks>

BoundAttributes.Name: ChildContent
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<exclude />
            <summary> 
            Gets or sets a value that indicates the child content for the button including HTML element. If the child content is not specified, button is rendered using <see cref="P:Syncfusion.Blazor.SplitButtons.ButtonGroupButton.Content" /> property. 
            </summary> 
            <value> 
            The template content. The default value is <c>null</c>. 
            </value> 
            <remarks> 
            The child content which is specified within <see cref="T:Syncfusion.Blazor.SplitButtons.ButtonGroupButton" /> tag directive is either a string or HTML Element. The string content is also specified using <see cref="P:Syncfusion.Blazor.SplitButtons.ButtonGroupButton.Content" /> property. 
            </remarks>

BoundAttributes.Name: CssClass
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary> 
            Gets or sets a value that indicates the CSS class string to customize the appearance of button. 
            </summary> 
            <value> 
            Accepts a CSS class string separated by space to customize the appearance of button. The default value is <c>String.Empty</c>. 
            </value>

BoundAttributes.Name: IconCss
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary> 
            Gets or sets a value that indicates the CSS class string to include an icon or image for the button.  
            </summary> 
            <value> 
            Accepts a CSS class string separated by space to include an icon or image for the button. The default value is <c>String.Empty</c>. 
            </value>

BoundAttributes.Name: Disabled
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary> 
            Gets or sets whether the button is disabled or not. 
            </summary> 
            <value> 
            <c>true</c>, if the button component is disabled. The default value is <c>false</c>. 
            </value>

BoundAttributes.Name: Selected
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary> 
            Gets or sets whether the component is selected or not. 
            </summary> 
            <value> 
            <c>true</c>, if the component is selected. The default value is <c>false</c>. 
            </value>

BoundAttributes.Name: Name
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary> 
            Gets or sets a value that indicates the name of the component. 
            </summary> 
            <value> 
            Accepts a string value. The default value is <c>String.Empty</c>. 
            </value> 
            <remarks> 
            The <see cref="P:Syncfusion.Blazor.SplitButtons.ButtonGroupButton.Name" /> property is used to set the name attribute of input element. 
            </remarks>

BoundAttributes.Name: Value
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary> 
            Gets or sets a value that indicates the value of the component. 
            </summary> 
            <value> 
            Accepts a string value. The default value is <c>String.Empty</c>. 
            </value>

<summary> 
            Gets or sets a value that indicates the child content for the dropdown button including HTML element. If the child content is not specified, Dropdown button is rendered using <see cref="P:Syncfusion.Blazor.SplitButtons.SfDropDownButton.Content" /> property. 
            </summary> 
            <value> 
            The template content. The default value is <c>null</c>. 
            </value> 
            <remarks> 
            The child content which is specified within <see cref="T:Syncfusion.Blazor.SplitButtons.SfDropDownButton" /> tag directive is either a string or HTML Element. The string content is also specified using <see cref="P:Syncfusion.Blazor.SplitButtons.SfDropDownButton.Content" /> property. 
            </remarks>

BoundAttributes.Name: Content
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary> 
            Gets or sets a value that indicates the content of dropdown button.
            </summary> 
            <value> 
            Accepts a string value. The default value is <c>String.Empty</c>. 
            </value> 
            <remarks> 
            Set child content within <see cref="T:Syncfusion.Blazor.SplitButtons.SfDropDownButton" /> tag directive, to render as HTML content. 
            </remarks>

BoundAttributes.Name: CssClass
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary> 
            Gets or sets a value that indicates the CSS class string to customize the appearance of dropdown button. 
            </summary> 
            <value> 
            Accepts a CSS class string separated by space to customize the appearance of dropdown button. The default value is <c>String.Empty</c>. 
            </value>

BoundAttributes.Name: IconCss
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary> 
            Gets or sets a a value that indicates the CSS class string to include an icon or image for the dropdown button.  
            </summary> 
            <value> 
            Accepts a CSS class string separated by space to include an icon or image for the dropdown button. The default value is <c>String.Empty</c>. 
            </value>

BoundAttributes.Name: IconPosition
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary> 
            Gets or sets a value that indicates how to display icons in the dropdown button. 
            </summary> 
            <value> 
            One of the <see cref="P:Syncfusion.Blazor.SplitButtons.SfDropDownButton.IconPosition" /> enumeration. The default value is <c>Left</c>.
            </value> 
            <remarks> 
            If the <c>IconPosition</c> is <c>Left</c>, the icon will be placed left to the content of the dropdown button. 
            If the <c>IconPosition</c> is <c>Right</c>, the icon will be placed right to the content of the dropdown button. 
            If the <c>IconPosition</c> is <c>Top</c>, the icon will be placed above the content of the dropdown button. 
            If the <c>IconPosition</c> is <c>Bottom</c>, the icon will be placed below the content of the dropdown button. 
            </remarks>

BoundAttributes.Name: Items
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary> 
            Gets or sets a value that indicates the the action items with its properties which will be rendered in dropdown button popup.  
            </summary> 
            <value> 
            Accepts a collection of <see cref="T:Syncfusion.Blazor.SplitButtons.DropDownMenuItem" /> object. The default value is <c>null</c>. 
            </value> 
            <remarks> 
            If the <c>Items</c> property is not specified, the dropdown button component is populated using <see cref="T:Syncfusion.Blazor.SplitButtons.DropDownMenuItems" /> and <see cref="T:Syncfusion.Blazor.SplitButtons.DropDownMenuItem" /> tag directives. 
            </remarks>

BoundAttributes.Name: Disabled
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary> 
            Gets or sets whether the dropdown button is disabled or not. 
            </summary> 
            <value> 
            <c>true</c>, if the dropdown button component is disabled. The default value is <c>false</c>. 
            </value>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnableRtl
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary> 
            Gets or sets whether the right to left direction is enabled for dropdown button. 
            </summary> 
            <value> 
            <c>true</c>, if the right to left direction is enabled for dropdown button. The default value is <c>false</c>. 
            </value>

BoundAttributes.Name: PopupContent
BoundAttributes.Documentation: Gets or sets a value that indicates the custom element as action items which will be rendered in DropDownButton popup. The template content. The default value is null. If the Items property and tag directive is not specified, the DropDownButton component is populated using . BoundAttributes.Documentation: Gets or sets a collection of additional attributes such as id, title etc. that will applied to the dropdown button container element. Additional attributes can be added by specifying as inline attributes or by specifying @attributes directive. TagHelpers.Name: Syncfusion.Blazor.SplitButtons.ProgressButtonAnimationSettings
TagHelpers.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the animation settings for the progress button.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Duration
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary> 
            Gets or sets a value that indicates the duration of the animation done in the progress button. 
            </summary> 
            <value> 
            Accepts a double value to set the duration of the animation of progress button. The default value is <c>400</c>. 
            </value>

BoundAttributes.Name: Easing
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary> 
            Gets or sets a value that indicates the animation timing function of the progress button component. 
            </summary> 
            <value> 
            <c>true</c>, if the progress UI is enabled. The default value is <c>false</c>. 
            </value>

BoundAttributes.Name: Effect
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary> 
            Gets or sets the animation effect of the progress button component. 
            </summary> 
            <value> 
            One of the <see cref="T:Syncfusion.Blazor.SplitButtons.AnimationEffect" /> enumeration. The default value is <see cref="F:Syncfusion.Blazor.SplitButtons.AnimationEffect.None" /> 
            </value> 
            <remarks> 
            If the <c>AnimationEffect</c> is <c>SlideLeft</c>, the content will be moved with slide left  animation. 
            If the <c>AnimationEffect</c> is <c>SlideRight</c>, the content will be moved with slide right animation. 
            If the <c>AnimationEffect</c> is <c>SlideUp</c>, the content will be moved with slide up animation. 
            If the <c>AnimationEffect</c> is <c>SlideDown</c>, the content will be moved with slide down animation. 
            If the <c>AnimationEffect</c> is <c>ZoomIn</c>, the content will be moved with zoom in  animation. 
            If the <c>AnimationEffect</c> is <c>ZoomOut</c>, the content will be moved with zoom out  animation 
            </remarks>

<summary>
            Specifies the floating label behavior of the SfMaskedTextBox that the placeholder text floats above the SfMaskedTextBox based on the following values.
            <para>Possible values are:</para>
            <list type="bullet">
            <item>
            <term>Never</term>
            <description>Never floats the label in the SfMaskedTextBox when the placeholder is available.</description>
            </item>
            <item>
            <term>Always</term>
            <description>The floating label always floats above the SfMaskedTextBox.</description>
            </item>
            <item>
            <term>Auto</term>
            <description>The floating label floats above the SfMaskedTextBox after focusing it or when enters the value in it.</description>
            </item>
            </list>
            </summary>

TagHelpers.Name: Syncfusion.Blazor.Inputs.SfSignature
TagHelpers.Documentation: Signature allows user to draw smooth signatures as vector outline of strokes using variable width Bézier curve interpolation. It allows to save signature as image. You can use your finger, pen, or mouse on a tablet, touchscreen, etc., to draw your own signature on this Signature component. Signature is a user interface to draw the signature or text. It supports stroke color, background color and image. In the below code example, a basic Signature initialized with tag directive. ]]>

BoundAttributes.Name: HtmlAttributes
BoundAttributes.Documentation: Gets or sets a collection of additional attributes that will applied to the component. Additional attributes can be added as inline attributes or by specifying @attributes directive. In the below code example, signature height and width has been specified as style attribute in . ]]>

BoundAttributes.Name: BackgroundColor
BoundAttributes.Documentation: Gets or sets the background color of the component. The background color of the component that accepts hex value, rgb and text (like red). The default value is null.

BoundAttributes.Name: BackgroundImage
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Gets or sets the background image for the <see cref="T:Syncfusion.Blazor.Inputs.SfSignature" /> component.
            </summary>
            <value>
            An image that used to fill the background of the component. The default value is <c>null</c>. 
            </value>

BoundAttributes.Name: Disabled
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Gets or sets whether to disable the <see cref="T:Syncfusion.Blazor.Inputs.SfSignature" /> component where the opacity is set to show disabled state. 
            </summary>
            <value>
            <c>true</c>, if the signature component is disabled for user interaction. The default value is <c>false</c>.
            </value>

BoundAttributes.Name: IsReadOnly
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Gets or sets whether to prevent the interaction in <see cref="T:Syncfusion.Blazor.Inputs.SfSignature" /> component. 
            </summary>
            <value>
            <c>true</c>, if the signature component is read only state where the user interaction is prevented. The default value is <c>false</c>.
            </value>

BoundAttributes.Name: SaveWithBackground
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Gets or sets whether to save the signature along with <see cref="P:Syncfusion.Blazor.Inputs.SfSignature.BackgroundColor" /> and <see cref="P:Syncfusion.Blazor.Inputs.SfSignature.BackgroundImage" /> while saving. 
            </summary>
            <value>
            <c>true</c>, if signature component to save with background. The default value is <c>true</c>.
            </value>

BoundAttributes.Name: StrokeColor
BoundAttributes.Documentation: Gets or sets the stroke color of the signature. The color of the signature stroke that accepts hex value, rgb and text (like red). The default value is "#000000".

BoundAttributes.Name: MinStrokeWidth
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Gets or sets the minimum stroke width for signature. 
            The <see cref="T:Syncfusion.Blazor.Inputs.SfSignature" /> component calculates stroke width based on <see cref="P:Syncfusion.Blazor.Inputs.SfSignature.Velocity" />, <see cref="P:Syncfusion.Blazor.Inputs.SfSignature.MinStrokeWidth" /> and <see cref="P:Syncfusion.Blazor.Inputs.SfSignature.MaxStrokeWidth" />.
            </summary>
            <value>
            The minimum width of stroke. The default value is <c>0.5</c>.
            </value>

BoundAttributes.Name: MaxStrokeWidth
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Gets or sets the maximum stroke width for signature.
            The <see cref="T:Syncfusion.Blazor.Inputs.SfSignature" /> component calculates stroke width based on <see cref="P:Syncfusion.Blazor.Inputs.SfSignature.Velocity" />, <see cref="P:Syncfusion.Blazor.Inputs.SfSignature.MinStrokeWidth" /> and <see cref="P:Syncfusion.Blazor.Inputs.SfSignature.MaxStrokeWidth" />.
            </summary>
            <value>
            The maximum width of stroke. The default value is <c>2.0</c>.
            </value>

BoundAttributes.Name: Velocity
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Gets or sets the velocity to calculate the stroke thickness based on the pressure of the contact on the digitizer surface.
            The Signature component calculates stroke thickness based on <see cref="P:Syncfusion.Blazor.Inputs.SfSignature.Velocity" />, <see cref="P:Syncfusion.Blazor.Inputs.SfSignature.MinStrokeWidth" /> and <see cref="P:Syncfusion.Blazor.Inputs.SfSignature.MaxStrokeWidth" />.
            </summary>
            <value>
            The velocity to calculate the stroke thickness based on the pressure of the contact on the digitizer surface. The default value is <c>0.7</c>.
            </value>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnablePersistence
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Gets or sets whether to persist component's state between page reloads.
            </summary>
            <value>
            <c>true</c>, if the component's state persistence is enabled. The default value is <c>false</c>.
            </value>
            <remarks>
            Component's property will be stored in browser local storage to persist component's state when page reloads.
            </remarks>

BoundAttributes.Name: Changed
BoundAttributes.Documentation: Gets or sets an event callback that is raised for the actions like undo, redo, clear and while user complete signing on component. @code { private void changefunc(SignatureChangeEventArgs args) { if (args.ActionName == "Clear") { // validation code goes here } } } ]]>

BoundAttributes.Name: OnSave
BoundAttributes.Documentation: Gets or sets an event callback that is raised while saving the signature. The file name and the file type(PNG, JPEG, SVG) can be changed using and . The event callback is raised only for the keyboard action (Ctrl + S). @code { private void beforesavefunc(SignatureSaveEventArgs args) { args.fileType = "SignatureFileType.Jpeg"; } } ]]>

BoundAttributes.Name: Created
BoundAttributes.Documentation: Gets or sets an event callback that is raised when component rendering is completed. You can load the pre-drawn signature when the signature component is created. In the below code example, the pre-drawn signature is loaded using Created event. @code { private void Created() { var sign = ""; // Base 64 or URL of the pre-drawn signature signature.LoadAsync(sign); } } ]]> Renders the base 64 string as signature on component. A Task that completes when the component has finished the loading of base 64 string. In the below code example, the pre-drawn signature is loaded using Created event. @code { private void Created() { var sign = ""; // Base 64 or URL of the pre-drawn signature signature.LoadAsync(sign, 400, 400); } } ]]>

TagHelpers.Name: Syncfusion.Blazor.Inputs.SfSlider<TValue>
TagHelpers.Documentation:
<summary>
            Partial class SfSlider.
            </summary>
            <typeparam name="TValue">Generic type parameter.</typeparam>.
            <summary>
            The Slider component allows the user to select a value or range of values
            in-between the min and max range, by dragging the handle over the slider bar.
            </summary>
            <summary>
            Partial class SfSlider.
            </summary>
            <summary>
            Specifies the partial class SfSlider.
            </summary>
            <summary>
            Specifies the partial class SfSlider.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: TValue
BoundAttributes.Documentation: Specifies the type of the type parameter TValue for the Syncfusion.Blazor.Inputs.SfSlider<TValue> component.

BoundAttributes.Name: ID
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Sets id attribute for the slider element.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ChildContent
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the ChildContent.
            </summary>
            <exclude />

BoundAttributes.Name: ValueExpression
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the expression for defining the value of the bound.
            </summary>
            <exclude />

BoundAttributes.Name: CssClass
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the custom classes to be added to the element used to customize the slider.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: CustomValues
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies an array of slider values in number or string type.
            The min and max step values are not considered.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnableAnimation
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Enables/Disables the animation for slider movement.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnablePersistence
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Enable or disable persisting component's state between page reloads.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnableRtl
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Enable or disable rendering component in right to left direction.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Enabled
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Enables or disables the slider.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Max
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the maximum value of the slider.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Min
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the minimum value of the slider.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Orientation
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
             Specifies whether to render the slider in vertical or horizontal orientation.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ReadOnly
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies whether the render the slider in read-only mode to restrict any user interaction.
            The slider rendered with user defined values and can’t be interacted with user actions.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ShowButtons
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies whether to show or hide the increase/decrease buttons
            of Slider to change the slider value.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Step
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the step value for each value change when the increase / decrease
             button is clicked or on arrow keys press or on dragging the thumb.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Type
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Defines the type of the Slider. The available options are:
              Default - Allows to a single value in the Slider.
              MinRange - Allows to select a single value in the Slider. It display’s a shadow from the start to the current value.
              Range - Allows to select a range of values in the Slider. It displays shadow in-between the selection range.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Value
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            It is used to denote the current value of the Slider.
            The value should be specified in array of number when render Slider type as range.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ValueChanged
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Gets or sets a callback of the bound value.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Width
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the width of the Slider.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: IsImmediateValue
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies whether the value need to be updated at the time of dragging slider handle.
            </summary>

TagHelpers.Documentation:
<summary>
            This class is used to set a tooltip for slider component.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ChildContent
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the ChildContent.
            </summary>
            <exclude />

BoundAttributes.Name: CssClass
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            It is used to customize the Tooltip which accepts custom CSS class names that define
             specific user-defined styles and themes to be applied on the Tooltip element.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Format
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            It is used to customize the Tooltip content to the desired format
             using internationalization or events (custom formatting).
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: IsVisible
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            It is used to show or hide the Tooltip of Slider Component.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Placement
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            It is used to denote the position for the tooltip element in the Slider. The available options are:
              Before - Tooltip is shown in the top of the horizontal slider bar or at the left of the vertical slider bar.
              After - Tooltip is shown in the bottom of the horizontal slider bar or at the right of the vertical slider bar.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ShowOn
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            It is used to determine the device mode to show the Tooltip.
            If it is in desktop, it will show the Tooltip content when hovering on the target element.
            If it is in touch device. It will show the Tooltip content when tap and holding on the target element.
            </summary>
